Dodo Village, Darfur. First terrace adjacent to Wadi Azum and beside a millet field, in light brown, sandy/gravelly soil. Loam clay. Alluvial and micaceous. Wadi Azum is the major wadi that goes as far as Chad. All others in the area feed it. Associated species: Cenchrus biflorus, Aristida sp., Acacia albida along wadi. These plants mature; mostly dried capsules.
